This paper focuses on the use of social media (specifically Facebook) as a tool for conducting large-scale surveys and identifying biases in the collected data. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories within computer science, including social media analysis (cs.SI), cyberpsychology (cs.CY), survey methodology (cs.SD), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), and computational social science (cs.CE). However, given the emphasis on survey methodology and the assessment of biases, cs.SD is the most likely sub-category, followed by cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.CE, and cs.HC.
